en_955558_0	The accidental explosion of an unserviceable device that had remained in the perimeter areas of Vasavilan Army Camp, Palaly killed one soldier and injured two soldiers who were engaged in some clearing work at dusk on Saturday (1).
en_955558_1	It is believed that the said explosive device had been left unattended underground in areas yet to be cleared at the time of the explosion.
en_955558_2	Police and Sri Lanka Corps of Military Police investigations are underway.
en_955558_3	Although over 97% of humanitarian demining has been already completed in the affected grounds giving priority to the areas of civilian habitation and land to be resettled, some land around the Army camps are yet to be cleared of explosives.
